festival.introText:
Music Nation presents

SOUTH EAST DANCE FEST

Music Nation is returning once again presenting the South East Dance Festival, a Music Festival dedicated to Old School Dance Music.

faqs.question: How much are South East Dance Festival tickets?
faqs.answer:
Early Entry Super Saver Ticket - £11.00 + booking fee 

Must join queue by 3pm or pay £10 door surcharge.

 

Early Entry Ticket - £12.45 + booking fee 

Must join queue by 4pm or pay £5 door surcharge.

 

Advance Discount Ticket - £15.00 + booking fee 

Last entry 6pm

 

VIP Ticket - £31.36 + booking fee 

Q Jump & access to VIP area with separate bar and toilets

faqs.question: When is South East Dance Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: South East Dance Festival takes place on Saturday 26th August 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to South East Dance Festival?
faqs.answer:
Arriving by Train:

Travelling to South East Dance Festival is extremely easy by train. The two local stations Southend Victoria or Southend Central are easily accessible from Central London. Whether you are travelling from outside or inside the London area, you will be able to find a train connection that will get you to the festival. For train travel to Southend Victoria or Central visit National Rail for up to the minute timetable and pricing information.

Arriving by Bus:

Whether you live in Southend, London or outside areas, once you arrive in the local area you may decide to commute to the festival via local buses. Getting a bus is straightforward as all you have to do is find the nearest stop for the 24 or 27 bus which will take you directly to Cokefield Avenue round the corner from the South East Dance Festival site in Garon Park. You can check out a local journey planner for bus travel.

Arriving by Car:

The address is :

Garon Park, Eastern Avenue, Southend on Sea, Essex, SS2 4FA.

Finding the festival by car - Garon Park is near to the following motorway junctions and A roads: A1159, A13, A127, A130, Junctions 28 & 29 of the M25.

 

 

You can check the website for more details.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where is South East Dance Festival?
faqs.answer: South East Dance Festival is held at Garon Park, Southend on Sea.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into South East Dance Festival?
faqs.answer: Licensing laws do not permit you to bring your own food and drink on site unless you have specific dietary requirements supported by a doctor’s note. There will be quality food available at the event from different food sellers and plenty of bars.

faqs.question: What medical assistance is available?
faqs.answer:
There is a medical first aid centre with qualified staff. Please identify the location on arrival.

There are lots of Marshall’s and Security on site who can be alerted to get medical help.

 

If you see anyone unwell please take them to the first aid area. If they are not able to be moved please contact a marshall or member of security as quickly as possible who will call for the necessary help. If you need to take medication regularly remember to bring it and let your friends know of any illness or allergies you may have.

faqs.question: What are the search and security policies?
faqs.answer:
You could be searched at the entrance for illegal items. If found they will be confiscated. Persons suspected of illegal activity will be searched and may be removed from the site.

Do not attempt to bring in illegal substances as you risk a strong chance of being caught.

The following items cannot be brought in to the ‘Soul Crusade’ site:

No! No offensive weapons

No! No fireworks, flares, laser pens or laser equipment.

No! No animals except guide dogs.

 

Please respect others. Anti-social behaviour could lead to being removed from the site.

 

Valuables

 

Keep your valuables safe. Carry money, credit cards, mobile phones, cameras, and anything else of value with you at all times. Don’t leave valuables where people can pick them up.

faqs.question: What facilities are available?
faqs.answer:
Toilets

There are plenty of toilets on site. Please keep toilets clean. Always wash your hands after using the toilets.

Rubbish and Waste

There are plenty of bins on site. Please use bins and not the floor.
